                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/8–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3940. For Villard. Embtel 4978 Aug. 17, 7 p.m.<note n="71" xml:id="d618fn71">Not
                        printed; it transmitted a form of a final act of the Conference approved by
                        the four delegations (881.00/8–1745).</note> You will be authorized to sign
                    or initial final act after approval of text by Dept.</p>
                <p>French invitation should be transmitted to Dept by the French Embassy in
                    Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
